This paper deals with a real-world multi-domain dialogue state tracking task, which involves natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a neural network that leverages external knowledge bases, which involves knowledge representation and reasoning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The use of similarities in an attribute space derived from the knowledge base suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Learning). The paper also deals with generating candidate slot keys and values, which involves information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible category. Finally, the use of external knowledge bases suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.DB (Databases).
